   1 + 2 + 4 + \cdots + 2^k = \frac{1 - 2^{k+1}}{1 - 2} 
S=1 + 2 + 4 + \cdots + 2^k  \\2S= 2 + 4 + \cdots + 2^k+2^{k+1}  \\S-2S=1-2^{k+1}  \\S(1-2)= 1-2^{k+1} \\S= \frac{1 - 2^{k+1}}{1 - 2}
